													"value": "Email-based name impersonation attacks are an evolving form of Business Email Compromise (BEC) that deceives the recipient into believing the email came from a trusted source. At Cloudflare, we detect and retract email-based name impersonation attacks every day from customer inboxes. While the vast majority of these are basic scams, such as asking for an employee to buy gift cards; more sophisticated attacks utilize new ways to leverage social engineering and OSINT to craft increasingly compelling phishing emails.",
